You have got to realize that the business managers wet dream is to be
able to hire a completely unskilled labor force on an hourly basis to
avoid paying benefits other than an hourly wage, with no critical
personel, except perhaps the business manager.

This is precisely why we see a huge interest in "application generators"
every so many years: it absolutely kills a business manager to have to
hire a skilled person.  It's an exercise in "Wouldn't it be nice if we
didn't need <name a skilled worker>?" -- and thus far has remained a
futile dream of software sales-persons everywhere.


