You seem to think I'm coming at this from a "typical UNIX guy" vector;
just because some of my statements can be taken to typify the attitude
of a "typical UNIX guy" as applied to an end user, don't fall into the
trap that lets you believe that I think there is a single UNIX vendor
anywhere who is marketing to end users in the first place.


The complaint that "UNIX vendors don't care about their end users" is
a total nonsequitor in the context of the current UNIX market.  As far
as UNIX vendors are concerned (in my opinion) there is no such thing
as an "end user" in the first place.


Whether or not this is "The Way Things Ought To Be" is an entirely
different argument: one that, if you want to argue it, requires a
different thread.


